.SH NAME
simple_shell - creates a simple shell
.nf
This simple shell program is executed by typing ./hsh
.br
Then, it will display a prompt ("$ ") and wait for a command as an input, such as command [arguments] [other]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.SH EXAMPLES
The following example demonstrates how to use \fB simple shell\fP:
./hsh [command] [options]
$ ls -l
.fi

/bin/ls
/bin/ls -a
ls
.fi

This will output:
.nf
(Your Files)
.fi
.SH BUGS
Simple shell only works one time, then has to be started again.

.SH AUTHOR
Joshua Lewis


